        "title": "fix(cron): warn on main heartbeat handoff ghost runs",
        "body": "Fixes #63106.\n\n## Summary\n- add a scoped warning for fast ok main-session systemEvent jobs using wakeMode=next-heartbeat\n- annotate cron run logs with possible-main-next-heartbeat-ghost-run for that handoff path\n- add cron.ghostRunWarningThresholdMs config with schema/help metadata and public docs\n\n## Tests\n- node --no-maglev node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts src/gateway/server-cron.test.ts\n- node --no-maglev node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.config.ts src/config/zod-schema.cron-retention.test.ts src/config/schema.base.generated.test.ts src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts src/cron/run-log.test.ts\n- node --import tsx scripts/generate-base-config-schema.ts --check\n- node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig tsconfig.oxlint.core.json src/gateway/server-cron.ts src/gateway/server-cron.test.ts src/config/types.cron.ts src/config/zod-schema.ts src/config/schema.help.ts src/config/schema.labels.ts src/cron/run-log.ts\n- git diff --check\n\nLatest PR-head verification also passed the full GitHub check set, with only neutral/skipped CodeQL remaining. Re-review retry note: the prior ClawSweeper run timed out before evaluating the latest proof/docs.\n\nNote: local tsgo checks currently fail before this change on unrelated dependency/type issues (missing typebox and existing model compat errors).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Verified that a fast successful main-session `systemEvent` cron handoff using `wakeMode: \"next-heartbeat\"` writes the `possible-main-next-heartbeat-ghost-run` warning into the cron run log.\n- Real environment tested: Local macOS checkout on this PR head, using the real `buildGatewayCronService` and real cron run-log reader with an isolated temporary `OPENCLAW_HOME`. This did not touch the real user cron store.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\n$ OPENCLAW_HOME=$(mktemp -d /tmp/openclaw-ghost-proof.XXXXXX) node --import tsx -e '... buildGatewayCronService(...); add main next-heartbeat systemEvent job; force run; readCronRunLogEntries(...)'\n```\n\n- Evidence after fix: Redacted terminal output from the isolated run-log proof:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"home\": \"/tmp/openclaw-ghost-proof.redacted\",\n  \"jobId\": \"redacted-job-id\",\n  \"logPath\": \"/tmp/openclaw-ghost-proof.redacted/runs/redacted-job-id.jsonl\",\n  \"latest\": {\n    \"action\": \"finished\",\n    \"status\": \"ok\",\n    \"summary\": \"proof handoff\",\n    \"runId\": \"cron:redacted-job-id:redacted-start-ms\",\n    \"durationMs\": 7,\n    \"deliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n    \"warnings\": [\n      \"possible-main-next-heartbeat-ghost-run\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The forced main-session `next-heartbeat` handoff completed successfully and the persisted run-log entry contains `warnings: [\"possible-main-next-heartbeat-ghost-run\"]`.\n- Public docs proof: The branch now documents `cron.ghostRunWarningThresholdMs` in `docs/cli/cron.md` and `docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md`, including the default `50` ms threshold and `0` to disable.\n- Additional gateway context: The same local machine also had a real running gateway reachable before this isolated proof (`openclaw gateway status` reported LaunchAgent loaded, runtime active, and connectivity probe ok).\n- Focused regression test: `server-cron.test.ts > buildGatewayCronService > warns and annotates fast main next-heartbeat systemEvent handoffs`.\n- What was not tested: I did not dispatch a real scheduled agent turn from the user's production cron store; the warning proof used an isolated temporary OpenClaw home with the real gateway cron service and run-log modules so it would not affect real scheduled jobs.\n",
